ghost and goth ready themselves for battle. goth draws his twin blasters, and 
in one fluid motion slams them onto his thighs, locking in the hip-mounted 
clips. 
ghost's body lifts a few inches above the ground and racks with electricity. 
he drops back down and fires two warning shots from his forearms into the air 
as a show of his abilities.
ghost: you ready for this? hell, we can't run this time, I say we send 
somebody to the C-R chamber for a looong time.
goth: COME OUT, PUNK! I CAN HIT YOU FROM WHERE YOU ARE, Y'KNOW! DON'T DIE 
COWERING IN THE BUSHES!

--part1_118.b42b2e8.297e1d16_boundary
